19/11/2010
WASHINGTON, United States -- Secretary of State Hillary Clinton is reiterating Washington's support for a direct dialogue between Kosovo and Serbia. 
During a press conference Wednesday (November 17th) in Washington, after meeting with British Foreign Secretary William Hague, Clinton said "We both are committed to helping the countries in the Balkans achieve full integration into the Euro-Atlantic community and we support a direct dialogue." Talks are expected to start after Kosovo holds elections on December 12th and forms its government institutions. 
(Express, Zeri, Kosova Sot, Lajm, Koha Ditore - 19/11/10)
